Key Match Events: Trezeguet scored in the 5th and 29th minutes for Egypt.
Mohamed Salah scored in the 56th minute for Egypt.
Fathi scored in the 90+4th minute for Egypt.
Majafi scored in the 50th minute for Botswana.
Mangolo scored in the 77th minute for Botswana.
Pre-Game Insights: Botswana is looking to record their first set of points in this AFCON qualifying campaign and their first-ever win against Egypt.
Botswana's only AFCON appearance came in 2012, and they lost all three matches in that tournament.
Didier Gomes Da Rosa was appointed as the head coach of Botswana in November ahead of the World Cup 2026 qualifiers.
Egypt, Africa's most successful side in the continental tournament, won 3-0 against Cape Verde in their first match of the AFCON qualifiers.
Egypt is currently top of Group C and hopes to extend their winning run in the AFCON qualifiers to six matches.
